HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL 
Fourth session   
Item 1 of the provisional agenda 
</p>
<p><b>ADOPTION OF THE AGENDA AND ORGANIZATION OF WORK 
</b></p>
<p><b>                             4/&#8230;.  Draft decision proposed by the President  
</b></p>
<p> </p>
<p><i> The Human Rights Council, 
</i></p>
<p><i> Recalling </i>General Assembly resolution 60/251, in particular its provisions relating to the 
</p>
<p>institution-building process of the Council, 
</p>
<p><i>1. Decides </i>to convene its fifth session from 11 to 18 June 2007, in order to consider 
</p>
<p>in particular the institution-building process of the Council; 
</p>
<p> 2. <i>Requests </i>the Secretary-General to provide the necessary support for the holding 
</p>
<p>of the fifth session of the Human Rights Council. 
</p>
